# The Gift of the Magi — O. Henry (adaptation, 2014, ASL 550)
# No published walkthrough exists — derived from game source (game.aslx).
# Guided-story engine: the complete Project Gutenberg text is cut into 50
# numbered beats driven by a game."Next text" counter; each beat is unlocked
# by ONE specific interaction (the status bar's "Next interaction" is the
# hint). Wrong-time interactions print "Nothing to see at this moment" etc.
# Custom verbs: flop on / look out / put on / take off / dialog / pay /
# take out / light / fix hair / sit at / hug / reach in pocket / unwrap.
# Movement is nameless exits driven by `go to <room>` (compass is hidden).
# Ending: beat #49 (dialog Jim on the couch) prints #49+#50 (the magi moral)
# and calls finish after an auto-continued "press any key" wait.
# No score, no RNG, no timers.
